Rational Logiscope Rule Violations Report    

Date: 01 Jul 2011

This document contains information concerning the coding rule analysis of the project Vishnu_1.2 made with Logiscope RuleChecker which is part of IBM® Rational® Logiscope.

The following information is available:

  • Violated Rules for the Application Vishnu_1.2
  • A synthesis table for Required rules for the Application Vishnu_1.2
  • A synthesis table for Advisory rules for the Application Vishnu_1.2

Rules Violated by the Application

The following orders are available for application analysis:

  • Violations ordered by File
  • Violations ordered by Rule/Severity

Total 12 0 0 0 0 0 0 0 0

Rules Description

MISRA_0_1_1 : Unreachable code

Severity is Required

 A project shall not contain unreachable code.

MISRA_0_1_3 : Unused variables

Severity is Required

 A project shall not contain unused variables.

MISRA_2_13_2 : Octal constants

Severity is Required

	Octal constants (other than zero) and octal escape 
sequences (other than "\0") shall not be used.

MISRA_2_13_4 : Literal suffixes

Severity is Required

	Literal suffixes shall be upper case.

MISRA_2_3_1 : Trigraphs

Severity is Required

 Trigraphs shall not be used.

MISRA_2_7_1 : character sequence within C-style comment

Severity is Required

The character sequence /* shall not be used within a C-style comment.

MISRA_2_7_2 : Commented out sections of code using C-style comments

Severity is Required

Sections of code shall not be "commented out" using 
C-style comments.

MISRA_2_7_3 : Commented out sections of code

Severity is Advisory

Sections of code should not be "commented out" using 
C++ comments.

MISRA_3_1_3 : Size of arrays

Severity is Required

When an array is declared, its size shall either be stated 
explicitly or defined implicitly by initialization.

MISRA_5_14_1 : Logical && or || operator

Severity is Required

The right hand operand of a logical && or || operator 
shall not contain side effects.

MISRA_5_18_1 : Comma operator

Severity is Required

	The comma operator shall not be used.

MISRA_5_2_10 : increment and decrement operators

Severity is Advisory

	The increment (++) and decrement (--) operators 
should not be mixed with other operators in an 
expression.

MISRA_5_2_11 : Overloading of operators

Severity is Required

The comma operator, && operator and the || operator 
shall not be overloaded.

MISRA_5_3_3 : Overload of unary & operator

Severity is Required

	The unary & operator shall not be overloaded.

MISRA_6_2_2 : Test of floating point expressions

Severity is Required

 Floating-point expressions shall not be directly or 
indirectly tested for equality or inequality.

MISRA_6_3_1 : Compound statement

Severity is Required

The statement forming the body of a switch, while, 
do ... while or for statement shall be a compound 
statement.

MISRA_6_4_1 : Compound statement for if

Severity is Required

An if ( condition ) construct shall be followed by 
a compound statement. The else keyword shall be 
followed by either a compound statement, or another if 
statement.

MISRA_6_4_5 : Throw or break in switch clauses

Severity is Required

An unconditional throw or break statement shall 
terminate every non-empty switch-clause.

MISRA_6_4_6 : Default clause in switch

Severity is Required

The final clause of a switch statement shall be the  default-clause.

MISRA_6_4_8 : At least one case in switch

Severity is Required

Every switch statement shall have at least one case-clause.

MISRA_6_5_1 : Type of loop counter

Severity is Required

	A for loop shall contain a single loop-counter which 
shall not have floating type.

MISRA_6_5_4 : Modification of loop counter

Severity is Required

	The loop-counter shall be modified by one of: --, ++, 
-=n, or +=n; where n remains constant for the duration 
of the loop.

MISRA_6_6_1 : Definition of label for goto

Severity is Required

	Any label referenced by a goto statement shall be 
declared in the same block, or in a block enclosing the 
goto statement.

MISRA_6_6_2 : Label of goto

Severity is Required

	The goto statement shall jump to a label declared later 
in the same function body.

MISRA_7_3_2 : Use of main

Severity is Required

The identifier main shall not be used for a function 
other than the global function main.

MISRA_7_3_3 : Unamed namespaces

Severity is Required

There shall be no unnamed namespaces in header files.

MISRA_7_4_3 : Assembly language

Severity is Required

Assembly language shall be encapsulated and isolated.

MISRA_7_5_2 : Address of automatic storage object

Severity is Required

The address of an object with automatic storage shall 
not be assigned to another object that may persist after 
the first object has ceased to exist.

MISRA_8_3_1 : Default arguments for overrided function

Severity is Required

Parameters in an overriding virtual function shall 
either use the same default arguments as the function 
they override, or else shall not specify any default 
arguments.

MISRA_8_4_1 : Ellipsis notation

Severity is Required

Functions shall not be defined using the ellipsis notation.

MISRA_8_4_3 : Explicit return statement

Severity is Required

All exit paths from a function with non-void return 
type shall have an explicit return statement with an 
expression.

MISRA_8_5_3 : Enumerator list

Severity is Required

	In an enumerator list, the = construct shall not be used 
to explicitly initialize members other than the first, 
unless all items are explicitly initialized.

MISRA_9_5_1 : Unions

Severity is Required

Unions shall not be used.

MISRA_9_6_2 : Bit-field type

Severity is Required

	Bit-fields shall be either bool type or an explicitly 
unsigned or signed integral type.

MISRA_9_6_4 : Length of bit-field

Severity is Required

	Named bit-fields with signed integer type shall have a 
length of more than one bit.

MISRA_10_2_1 : Accessible entities in multiple inheritance hierarchy

Severity is Advisory

	All accessible entity names within a multiple 
inheritance hierarchy should be unique.

MISRA_10_3_3 : Overriding a virtual function

Severity is Required

	A virtual function shall only be overridden by a pure 
virtual function if it is itself declared as pure virtual.

MISRA_12_1_3 : Constructors

Severity is Required

All constructors that are callable with a single 
argument of fundamental type shall be declared explicit.

MISRA_15_0_2 : Exception object

Severity is Advisory

	An exception object should not have pointer type.

MISRA_15_0_3 : Use of goto and switch in try catch block

Severity is Required

	Control shall not be transferred into a try or catch block 
using a goto or a switch statement.

MISRA_15_1_1 : Exception in exception

Severity is Required

	The assignment-expression of a throw statement shall 
not itself cause an exception to be thrown.

MISRA_15_1_2 : NULL thrown

Severity is Required

NULL shall not be thrown explicitly.

MISRA_15_1_3 : Empty throw

Severity is Required

	An empty throw (throw;) shall only be used in the 
compound-statement of a catch handler.

MISRA_15_3_7 : Try-catch statement

Severity is Required

	Where multiple handlers are provided in a single 
try-catch statement or function-try-block, any ellipsis 
(catch-all) handler shall occur last.

MISRA_15_5_1 : Class destructor

Severity is Required

	A class destructor shall not exit with an exception.

MISRA_15_5_3 : Call of terminate function

Severity is Required

	The terminate() function shall not be called implicitly.

MISRA_16_0_1 : Include directive

Severity is Required

	#include directives in a file shall only be preceded by 
other preprocessor directives or comments.

MISRA_16_0_2 : Definition of macros

Severity is Required

	Macros shall only be #define'd or #undef'd in the global namespace.

MISRA_16_0_3 : #undef

Severity is Required

	#undef shall not be used.

MISRA_16_0_5 : Arguments to a function-like macro

Severity is Required

	Arguments to a function-like macro shall not contain 
tokens that look like preprocessing directives.

MISRA_16_0_6 : Parameters of function like macro

Severity is Required

In the definition of a function-like macro, each instance 
of a parameter shall be enclosed in parentheses, unless 
it is used as the operand of # or ##.

MISRA_16_0_8 : # token

Severity is Required

If the # token appears as the first token on a line, then it 
shall be immediately followed by a preprocessing token.

MISRA_16_1_1 : Defined preprocessor operator

Severity is Required

The defined preprocessor operator shall only be used in 
one of the two standard forms.

MISRA_16_1_2 : Preprocessor directives

Severity is Required

All #else, #elif and #endif preprocessor directives shall 
reside in the same file as the #if or #ifdef directive to 
which they are related.

MISRA_16_2_3 : Include guards

Severity is Required

Include guards shall be provided.

MISRA_16_2_4 : Characters in header file name

Severity is Required

	The ', ", /* or // characters shall not occur in a header file name.

MISRA_16_2_5 : Header file name

Severity is Advisory

	The \ character should not occur in a header file name. 
[Undefined	2.8(2)]

MISRA_16_2_6 : include directive

Severity is Required

	The #include directive shall be followed by either a 
<filename> or "filename" sequence. 
[Undefined	16.2(4)]

MISRA_16_3_1 : occurences of # and ##

Severity is Required

 There shall be at most one occurrence of the # or ## 
operators in a single macro definition. 
[Unspecified 16.3.2(2), 16.3.3(3), Undefined 16.3.2(2), 16.3.3(3)]

MISRA_17_0_2 : Standard library macros and objects

Severity is Required

The names of standard library macros and objects shall not be reused.

MISRA_17_0_3 : Standard library functions

Severity is Required

The names of standard library functions shall not be overridden.

MISRA_17_0_5 : setjmp and longjmp

Severity is Required

The setjmp macro and the longjmp function shall not be 
used.

MISRA_18_0_1 : C library

Severity is Required

	The C library shall not be used.

MISRA_18_0_2 : atof, atoi and atol

Severity is Required

The library functions atof, atoi and atol from library 
<cstdlib> shall not be used.

MISRA_18_0_4 : Time handling functions

Severity is Required

	The time handling functions of library <ctime> shall not 
be used.

MISRA_18_2_1 : macro offsetof

Severity is Required

The macro offsetof shall not be used.

cmdef : Classes in code file

Severity is Required


Definition:
-----------
A code file must not contain any class declaration.

Parameters:
-----------
A string representing the types of modules (metric type) that should 
be considered as code files.

dmaccess : Access to members data

Severity is Advisory


Definition:
-----------
The class interface must be purely functional: members data definitions can be 
limited.

Parameters:
----------
A list of character strings corresponding to the forbidden access specifiers for 
the data members.

Justification:
--------------
The good way to modify the state of an object is via its methods, not its data 
members.
The data members of a class should be private or at least protected.

Example:
--------

In order to prevent the use of data members in the public and protected 
access specifiers, the standard may be expressed as below:
STANDARD dmaccess ON LIST "public" "protected" EN LIST END STANDARD

fntype : Function types

Severity is Advisory


Definition:
-----------
Each function has to declare its type. If nothing is returned, 
it must be declared of void type.

inlinevirt : Inline Virtual Functions

Severity is Advisory


Definition:
-----------
Virtual functions shall not be declared inline.
(This rule relates to Item 24 in "More Effective C++", Scott Meyers).

Justification:
--------------
Improves code efficiency.

normalnew : Avoid Hiding the "Normal" Form of "new"

Severity is Advisory


Definition:
-----------
If operator new is declared one or several times inside a class, at least one of
these declarations shall follow the "normal" form:
- the type of the first parameter shall be size_t;
- all other parameters, if any, shall have a default value.
(This rule relates to Item 9 in "Effective C++", Scott Meyers).

Justification:
--------------
Lets the usual invocation form of new available.
